main event: A civilian on a Danish ship observed an unidentified aerial phenomenon described as a 'planet' flying at very high altitude and fast speed in the Atlantic Ocean on November 6, 1953, lasting for four minutes. The report concluded that the light was evaluated as an astronomical phenomenon.
interesting points: The observation was categorized as a ground visual type with no reported physical evidence or photographs.
The source of the report was a civilian on a Danish ship, adding credibility to the observation.
The object was initially described as a 'planet' moving at very high speed and altitude, behaviors uncommon for planets.
The report was captured as part of Project Blue Book, an Air Force program that investigated UFO phenomena.
The report concluded that the observation was evaluated as an astronomical phenomenon, potentially indicating a natural explanation.
sighted object: unidentified aerial phenomenon described as a 'planet'
